<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE BUCKS CAN'T STOP 'EM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE _ They are nearly halfway to reaching an unreachable
record, and 35 days removed from their last loss, yet the Los
Angeles Lakers march onlike a team that has no peer, still looking
for someone to challenge their preeminence.
</P>
<P>
   Another presumed obstacle the high-powered, high-scoring
Milwaukee Bucks fell to the wayside Wednesday night, and the Lakers
simply zoomed on, pocketing their 16th straight win 103-94 at the
Bradley Center.
</P>
<P>
   A fun little streak that once served as an innocuous
conversation piece is now taking on serious proportions
</P>
<P>
   tying the second-longest winning streak in franchise history,
and moving the Lakers within a mere 17 victories of the NBA record.
</P>
<P>
   Now it seems like momentum alone is pushing them onward.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, I just didn't believe that we were going to win the game
that easily,'' coach Phil Jackson remarked. ``I thought it was
going to be a difficult game.''
</P>
<P>
   It was supposed to be, as were many other such matchups since
Dec. 8 the date of the Lakers' last loss. But they have not let The
Streak delude them, the Lakers played consistent defense and held
the Bucks to 39.7 percent shooting and 10 points below their
average.
</P>
<P>
   All this against a team that scored 137 points two nights
earlier and beat the Charlotte Hornets by 50. And yet the Lakers
!ital!still didn't think much of the accomplishment.
</P>
<P>
   ``It just means we're playing good ball,'' Robert Horry said.
``You look at that (streak), you have to really analyze how many
.500 teams did we beat during that stretch. I think it's only like
four. ...
</P>
<P>
   ``(The Bucks) didn't rebound well. . . . They're an
offensive-minded team. Their defense rank, what, 28? When we go up
against a team that's in the top 10, then we can talk.''[p Picky,
picky. Two more wins, though, and the Lakers will have equaled the
18-game streak that Jackson's Chicago Bulls achieved during the
1995-96 championship season.
</P>
<P>
   Win No. 16 was much like the ones before it plenty of Shaquille
O'Neal (27 points, 10 rebounds), Kobe Bryant (22 points, five
assists, three steals) and Glen Rice (20 points). But the Lakers
got healthy support from the role players as well, as Ron Harper
got 16 points on 5-of-7 shooting and Horry and Derek Fisher pitched
in seven points each off the bench.
</P>
<P>
   That was more than enough to overcome the Bucks' potent trio of
Sam Cassell, Ray Allen and Glenn Robinson, who combined for 71
points but got little support from their teammates, particularly on
defense, particularly in the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Cassell's 16 points propelled the Bucks to a nine-point lead in
the first half, but the Lakers with Bryant, O'Neal, Rice and Harper
all in double figures took a 56-48 lead by halftime, and they never
relinquished the lead.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're just showing that they are the best team in the
league,'' said Allen, who beat out Bryant for a spot on the Olympic
team. ``Phil Jackson has imposed his will on them, and they just go
out and win every night.''
</P>
<P>
   A third-quarter burst put it away. The Lakers had their lead cut
to four, but Bryant hit a reverse and a technical foul shot and
Rice drained consecutive 3-pointers for a 9-0 run and a 75-62
advantage.
</P>
<P>
   They opened the fourth quarter with a 10-2 run that made it a
21-pointgame, and the Bucks never challenged again.
</P>
<P>
   It looked ridiculously easy,too.
</P>
<P>
   ``It seems easy,'' Bryant said, ``but it just comes down to
working hard, man. The more you work at it, the better you get
it.''
</P>
<P>
   So the Lakers continue to march toward 33 wins, whether they
intend to or not, whether they can make it or not. But they won't
make it a goal.[ep ``Nope,'' O'Neal said. ``The `bling-bling' is
the goal. You know what bling-bling is? Imagine a ring, hitting the
light, the diamonds, `bling-bling.' `Bling-bling, that's all we
want.' ''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-13-00 0203EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
