r e BC-MOVIES-MRSMITH14-COX     01-13 0231
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIES-MRSMITH14-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Reel alternatives
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Mr. Smith Goes to
</P>
<P>
   Washington'' (unrated)
</P>
<P>
   James Stewart teams up with his ``It's a Wonderful Life''
director, Frank Capra, in this classic 1939 comedy-drama, playing
an idealist who learns firsthand how underhanded politics can
become.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Girl With Brains
</P>
<P>
   in Her Feet'' (unrated)
</P>
<P>
   The High Museum of Art presents this coming-of-age drama about a
biracial teenage girl, trying to balance an uneasy home life with
her desire to become a track star. Part of the museum's series
featuring selected titles from ``Changing the Guard: The Festival
of New British Cinema.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Queer as Folk'' (unrated)
</P>
<P>
   IMAGE Film and Video Center presents this controversial,
sexually frank (and very popular) British TV miniseries about three
gay men in a British town. Presented in eight half-hour episodes.
</P>
<P>
   WEEKNIGHT SCREENINGS
</P>
<P>
   ``Little Dieter Needs to Fly'' (unrated)
</P>
<P>
   The Goethe-Institut Atlanta presents Werner Herzog's 1997
documentary about Dieter Dengler, a former German with a lifelong
dream to fly, who became an American pilot who was shot down and
captured during the Vietnam War.
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
