<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: DAYTONA BEACH, FLA. 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ INFORMATION: The Daytona Beach Area Convention &AMP; Visitors
Bureau can provide a free 92-page vacation planner that features
information on attractions, lodging and dining. Call 800-544-0415;
access www.daytonabeach.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ LODGING: Daytona Beach has more than 400 hotels and motels,
with prices to suit every budget. The area also has many
campgrounds and recreational vehicle parks. The visitors bureau can
provide a list of accommodations and campsites.
</P>
<P>
   Particularly appealing are properties that participate in the
Superior Small Lodging program. These small hotel, motels and inns
_ all with 75 or fewer rooms _ must pass annual inspections with
criteria for cleanliness, comfort, privacy and safety. For a
brochure describing each property, call 800-854-1234; access
www.daytonalodging.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ DAYTONA 500: The Daytona 500 will be held Feb. 20. While the
race is officially sold out, a small number of entertainment
packages that include race seats are available. Call 904-947-6475.
</P>
<P>
   Several other races will held in conjunction with the Daytona
500 beginning on Feb. 12. Tickets remain for these events. Call
904-254-2700; access www.daytonaintlspeedway.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ CONTACTS: Here are some other numbers and Web sites for
vacation planning purposes:
</P>
<P>
   _ A Tiny Cruise Line: 904-226-2343
</P>
<P>
   _ Sunny Daze and Starry Night Cruises: 904-253-1796
</P>
<P>
   _ Main Street Pier: 904-238-1212
</P>
<P>
   _ Adventure Landing: 904-258-0071
</P>
<P>
   _ Ponce de Leon Inlet Lighthouse: 904-761-1821;
www.ponceinlet.org
</P>
<P>
   _ The Casements: 904-676-3216
</P>
<P>
   _ Bethune-Cookman College: 904-255-1401; www.bethune.cookman.edu
</P>
<P>
   _ Museum of Arts and Sciences: 904-255-0285; www.moas.org
</P>
<P>
   _ Daytona Iceplex: 904-304-8400
</P>
<P>
   _ Daytona USA: 904-947-6800; www.daytonausa.com
</P>
