<P>
   Editors:
</P>
<P>
   Newspapers that used ONLINE-MUSIC by Sara Robinson, which moved
Tuesday, Jan. 11, will wish to use the following correction.
</P>
<P>
   Because of an editing error, an article and headline from the
New York Times News Service about a new Internet service for
downloading and listening to digital music incorrectly
characterized the service. The service, provided by MP3.com of San
Diego, will enable customers to store music online. While the
service may make it easier for customers to swap copyrighted music,
it is not intended to facilitate the swapping of music.
</P>
