   Mifune: A Danish business whiz has to amuse his mentally ill
brother after their father dies. He does so by pretending to be
Japanese samurai movie star Toshiro Mifune. Another one of those
Scandinavian Dogma productions, so it probably looks pretty funky.
(Sony Pictures Classics)
</P>
<P>
   Reindeer Games: John Frankenheimer tries to thrill us again with
a story of a criminal who wants to start a new life ... but they
just keep pulling him back in. Ben Affleck, Gary Sinise and
Charlize Theron star. (Miramax)
</P>
<P>
   The Terrorist: Indian feature based on the assassination of
Prime Minister Rajiv Ghandi. Presented by that unpredictable John
Malkovich. (Phaedra Cinema)
</P>
<P>
   Three Strikes: California's crime law gets its first comic
treatment. Brian Hooks stars as a young man just out of prison who
finds himself falsely implicated in a crime. Facing 25 years in
prison, he flees. Wacky adventures ensue. (MGM) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
