UNDATED: ... Shakespeare's melancholy Dane. (MGM Classics) March 10:
<TEXT>
<P>
   Deterrence: It's election night 2008. The president (Kevin
Pollak) is snowbound in a Colorado diner. Suddenly, an
international incident threatens nuclear apocalypse. Nervous yet?
Directorial debut of film critic Rod Lurie. (Paramount Classics)
</P>
<P>
   Kadosh: Israeli film follows the struggles of two sisters at
odds with their strict, Orthodox Jewish culture. (Kino
International)
</P>
<P>
   Mission to Mars: The first manned mission to the Red Planet gets
in trouble, so another bunch of astronauts have to go help. Brian
De Palma directs Gary Sinise, Don Cheadle, Jerry O'Connell, Kim
Delaney and Tim Robbins. (Touchstone)
</P>
<P>
   My Best Fiend: Wacko German director Werner Herzog's homage to
his even loonier late star, Klaus Kinski. (New Yorker Films) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   March 17
</P>
<P>
   Condo Painting: Not about home improvement, but a documentary on
artist George Condo. (USA Films)
</P>
<P>
   Erin Brockovich: Julia Roberts teams with director Steven
Soderbergh to dramatize the true story of a file clerk who stumbles
upon a cover-up involving contaminated water in the small
California desert town of Hinckley. Think of it as ``A Civil
Action'' with sex appeal. (Universal)
</P>
<P>
   Final Destination: High school kid has premonition, jumps off
plane, plane crashes, death seems to stalk him in the aftermath.
(New Line Cinema)
</P>
<P>
   Trash: The 30-year-old Andy Warhol, um, trash classic. Actually
directed by Paul Morrissey. (Jour de Fete Films) &QL; 
