<SLUG> BC-MOVIES-2000-LIST-LADN, </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 2nd add  
UNDATED: ... Cathy Moriarty and RuPaul. (Fine Line Features)
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Carriers Are Waiting: Black-and-white Belgian film about a
modern-day Don Quixote and his quest for a four-door sedan.
(Artisan Entertainment)
</P>
<P>
   Crime and Punishment in Suburbia: Dostoyevsky gets the teen
treatment. (United Artists)
</P>
<P>
   Head Over Heels: New York City art restorer thinks she's finally
found a man who won't cheat her. Problem is, he might kill her.
It's a comedy. Monica Potter and Freddie Prinze Jr. star.
(Universal)
</P>
<P>
   Highway 395: Fred Dryer plays a cop. (Fred Dryer Productions)
</P>
<P>
   Small Time Crooks: Call it ``Take the Money and Run,'' 30 years
later. Woody Allen and Tracey Ullman play a crooked couple with
dreams of a big-city bank robbery. Allen wrote and directed the
film, naturally. (DreamWorks)
</P>
<P>
   Soft Fruit: Four squabbling siblings return home to their small
Australian town to care for their ailing mother. Bickering and
reconciliations ensue. (Fox Searchlight)
</P>
<P>
   Sunshine: Three generations of Hungarian Jews try to make it
through the 20th century. Acclaimed director Istvan Szabo wrote the
screenplay with playwright Israel Horovitz. Ralph Fiennes, William
Hurt and Rosemary Harris star. (Paramount Classics)
</P>
<P>
   Texas Rangers: Not the baseball team, but the rugged band of
law-enforcing cowboys trying to keep the West safe from desperado
types. (Miramax)
</P>
<P>
   Untitled Cameron Crowe Project: Crowe follows up ``Jerry
Maguire'' with this semi-autobiographical story of a 15-year-old
music fan who lands an assignment from Rolling Stone to cover an
up-and-coming band. No doubt, a rite of passage (or three) may
occur. (DreamWorks)
</P>
<P>
   The Virgin Suicides: The directing debut of Sofia Coppola _ yes,
Francis' daughter _ is an adaptation of Jeffrey Eugenides' novel of
teen-age longing and suburban dysfunction in the 1970s. James
Woods, Kathleen Turner and Kirsten Dunst star. (Paramount Classics)
</P>
<P>
   Woman on Top: Romantic fable about a woman whose culinary
