UNDATED: ... more fun than ``Random Hearts.'' (Miramax)
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cecil B. Demented: John Waters returns with this comedy about a
group of independent film nuts who kidnap a prominent Hollywood
star and force her to act in their low-budget movie. Bowfinger
would be proud. (Artisan)
</P>
<P>
   The Golden Bowl: The Merchant Ivory team takes on Henry James
again in this tale of romantic deceit set in Europe. Kate
Beckinsale, Anjelica Huston, Nick Nolte, Jeremy Northam and Uma
Thurman star. (Miramax)
</P>
<P>
   The Legend of Bagger Vance: Matt Damon and Will Smith star in
Robert Redford's adaptation of Steven Pressfield's novel about a
mysterious caddy (Smith) who helps a troubled World War I hero
(Damon) master the games of golf and life. (DreamWorks)
</P>
<P>
   Loser: Two New York University dweebs (``American Pie's'' Jason
Biggs and Mena Suvari) unite against their oppressors, fall in
love. Written and directed by ``Clueless''' Amy Heckerling.
(Columbia)
</P>
<P>
   Requiem for a Dream: Darren Aronofsky, the director of ``Pi,''
comes back for another helping. Here he adapts Hubert Selby Jr.'s
novel about a young dreamer making his way through a dark world.
Ellen Burstyn and Jared Leto star. (Artisan)
</P>
<P>
   Road Trip: College student travels 1,800 miles to save lifelong
romance. He brings three of his buddies along for moral support and
gas money. (DreamWorks)
</P>
<P>
   Shanghai Noon: Jackie Chan does the Wild West. (Touchstone)
</P>
<P>
   State and Main: David Mamet comedy(!) about shooting a movie in
a small New England town. Crack cast includes Alec Baldwin, Charles
Durning, William H. Macy, Sarah Jessica Parker, Julia Stiles and
Philip Seymour Hoffman. (Fine Line Features)
</P>
<P>
   The Way of the Gun: ``Usual Suspects'' screenwriter Christopher
McQuarrie makes his directorial debut in this story about the
kidnapping of a pregnant surrogate mother. Ryan Phillipe, Benicio
Del Toro, James Caan and Juliette Lewis star. (Artisan) &QL; 
