<HEADLINE>
GOT QUESTIONS, NEED ANSWERS ON COWOBYS, MAVERICKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY GALLOWAY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
Got plenty of questions. Need help with the answers.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Has Dot Com Cuban changed his mind yet about using Jerry Jones
as his ownership role model?
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Cuban, may I suggest Tom Hicks instead?
</P>
<P>
   Has Jesse Jackson's group filed a civil rights' protest yet over
the Chan Gailey firing?
</P>
<P>
   It's not just about color, is it, Jesse?
</P>
<P>
   Joe Avezzano?
</P>
<P>
   Isn't Coach Joe tight with Troy and tight with Jerry? Aren't
Troy and Jerry the head-coach makers and breakers at Valley Ranch?
</P>
<P>
   Isn't that what's wrong with the Cowboys to start with?
</P>
<P>
   Hasn't Coach Joe dealt with all segments of the locker room as
special teams' coach? It's true, isn't it, he's respected and liked
by the players?
</P>
<P>
   Doesn't Coach Joe love to run up and down the sidelines,
screaming and gesturing? Don't the fans love an ``emotional''
coach?
</P>
<P>
   Isn't Jerry Jones whistling ``Moon Over Miami'' if he thinks any
competent coach from the outside would take the Cowboys' job?
</P>
<P>
   Is this a suggestion Jones should promote Avezzano to head
coach?
</P>
<P>
   Wouldn't Jones immediately eliminate any name endorsed by this
space?
</P>
<P>
   Who said anything about hiring Coach Joe? You never read that
here, now did you?
</P>
<P>
   Since Dot Com Cuban wants to sign Dennis Rodman, will he also
hear me out on giving Roy Tarpley a second chance?
</P>
<P>
   Or would that be more like a sixth chance? Seventh?
</P>
<P>
   Didn't a local general manager say last week, ``We're finished
spending?''
</P>
<P>
   Didn't a local owner answer that with, ``No, you're not.''
</P>
<P>
   Didn't Doug Melvin then sign pitcher Darren Oliver?
</P>
<P>
   Can you remember the last time an owner refused to spend less?
</P>
<P>
   Didn't I tell you, Mr. Cuban, to be more like Hicks?
</P>
<P>
   Did I read this right? Aaron Sele turned down $28 million from
the Rangers and eventually had to settle for $15 million from the
Mariners?
</P>
<P>
   Is my math right? Did Sele cost himself $13 million in one week?
</P>
<P>
   Will Kenny Rogers accept my apology for calling him the dumbest
pitcher the Rangers ever had?
</P>
<P>
   How exactly did Sele's agent explain this little screwup to
Aaron?
</P>
<P>
   Given the choice of keeping only one, would it have been Chan
Gailey as coach or Jerry Jones as general manager?
</P>
<P>
   When Jones seeks an honest and private opinion from Troy, does
Aikman ever look him in the eye and say, ``Jerry, stop being an
idiot?''
</P>
<P>
   Who would Avezzano hire as his offensive coordinator?
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Rhome?
</P>
<P>
   That names sounds familiar _ didn't Aikman love Rhome when Jerry
was quarterback coach here way back in '89?
</P>
<P>
   Why have I seen at least a hundred replays of the ``Music City
Miracle'' and still think Buffalo was jobbed?
</P>
<P>
   Why do all these people keep saying the play was legal? What
exactly are they watching?
</P>
<P>
   Does Lindy Ruff also cry over football?
</P>
<P>
   The referee in Nashville last week who made the instant replay
decision against the Bills _ doesn't he live in Irving?
</P>
<P>
   Don't the Stars office and practice in Irving?
</P>
<P>
   Why am I laughing?
</P>
<P>
   Did you get a good look at the Stanley Cup as it made the local
rounds last summer? Got your picture taken with it, didn't you?
</P>
<P>
   Come next summer, all we're gonna have of the Stanley Cup around
here will be our memories _ don't you think?
</P>
<P>
   Are you as excited as I am about seeing Nine-Toed Deion in the
Pro Bowl?
</P>
<P>
   Did you ever think there'd be a time when Nine Toed made a
better columnist than player?
</P>
<P>
   Wasn't it Jim Reeves who asked if Deion counted against the
``Star-Telegram'' salary cap?
</P>
<P>
   What salary cap, Revo?
</P>
<P>
   John G. Dooley?
</P>
<P>
   What was the biggest sports story this week _ Gailey being fired
or John G. resigning as the only race caller Lone Star Park ever
had?
</P>
<P>
   You already know my answer, don't you?
</P>
<P>
   Can I just say how much I'm going to miss Dooley bringing home
the horses next summer? Can I also say, good luck to John calling
the races in Chicago?
</P>
<P>
   Is it backstabbing if the owner asks if you're happy with the
offensive system and the quarterback tells him the truth?
</P>
<P>
   Does the QB realize what a P.R. bloodbath he just took? Does he
care?
</P>
<P>
   Is Dot Com Cuban really serious about this Rodman thing?
</P>
<P>
   If he is, shouldn't we really have to wonder if those good first
impressions are now null and void?
</P>
<P>
   Have I mentioned that Stephen Jones' name is constantly uttered
in reverent-like tones around Valley Ranch these days? What's this
_ the No. 1 son being viewed as the eventual savior?
</P>
<P>
   You're guessing then that Stephen must take after his mother?
</P>
<P>
   Many questions. So few answers.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
