granted that utility stocks always fall when interest rates rise.
After all, electric companies borrow a lot of money, and thus
suffer when rates rise, and their shares appeal only to the
diminishing band of investors who value dividends. So it is worth
asking why the stocks are rising. By Floyd Norris.
