<P>
   LAPD-RECRUIT (Los Angeles) -- The Los Angeles Police Department
is looking for a few hundred good officers, and officials said
Thursday they are willing to begin paying a $2,000 relocation fee
to get them. With the number of officers leveling off at nearly
9,500, officials are concerned that high attrition rates caused
partly by other police agencies hiring away LAPD officers -- and
the difficulty in hiring new officers could take it down to the
9,000 level. To counter that, the department is beginning an
aggressive recruiting drive in Los Angeles and out of state to hire
the new officers needed tomaintain its current size as well as hire
the 157 new officers needed to keep a federal grant. By Rick Orlov
(Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news wires.)
</P>
<P>
   DENTAL-FRAUD (Los Angeles) -- Convictions of dental billing
fraud increased in '99, and state authorities said Wednesday
they'll continue their efforts to prosecute dentists who
participate in fraudulent billing practices. According to state
officials, more than 57 investigations of Denti-Cal dentists are
currently underway, and the Attorney General's office has promised
to prosecute any dentist suspected of defrauding the state. By
Chris Sieroty (Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national
news wires.)
