<P>
   BASKETBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HAWKS-JACKSON - ATLANTA - When the Atlanta Hawks traded for
Isaiah Rider last summer, the team insisted that Portland also
include Jim Jackson as an insurance policy. Thirty-three games into
the season, Jackson has emerged as the key player in the deal.
Rider has been suspended twice and has missed practice on several
occasions while Jackson has been a consistent scorer throughout the
season. After a strange NBA career that has included six teams in
the last four seasons, Jackson finally appears to have found a home
with the Hawks. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22. MOVED.
WITH PHOTO.
