<P>
   TERRY-LUMBER (Los Angeles) -- Family owned Terry Lumber Co., a
big player in the post World War II building boom in the San
Fernando Valley, is being sold to a North Carolina company,
officials said on Thursday. Terry was formed in 1949 and is
considered one of the top building materials suppliers in Southern
California. The Tarzana-based company has 1999 sales of $250
milion. Few changes are planned at the company. In recent years it
was led by Tom Mullin, the son of the founder. Mullin died last
summer. By Chris Sieroty (Will move on the ``f'' financial news
wire.)
