<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-13 21:00 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5520 &Cx1f; taf-z
u i BC-MEXICO-SINGER-NYT &LR;      01-13 0585
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MEXICO-SINGER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FUGITIVE MEXICAN SINGER SOUGHT IN SEX CASE IS ARRESTED IN BRAZIL  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   By JULIA PRESTON   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY _ The last time that the pop star known as Gloria
Trevi performed on television in Mexico, she pranced and tossed her
mane of wavy hair with the carefree defiance that made her an icon
of rebellion among young girls.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday the artist was back on television again. Looking
subdued and wearing a gray T-shirt in place of her old sequined
halter top, Ms. Trevi was caught by cameras in Rio de Janiero,
Brazil, where she was arrested on charges of corrupting minors.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Trevi's longtime manager, Andrade Sanchez, was also
arrested, along with another singer in the case, Maria Raquel
Portillo. Andrade is accused of forcing sex upon several young
girls who were among his teen-age proteges.
</P>
<P>
   He and Ms. Trevi dropped from view over a year ago, but they
have been fugitives from justice since arrest warrants were issued
against them in Mexico last November.
</P>
<P>
   Mexico immediately initiated extradition proceedings Thursday.
In statements to the police in Brazil, both Ms. Trevi and Andrade
denied the charges.
</P>
<P>
   The scandal has burned hot in Mexico for many months, exposing
the underside of an insular entertainment world filled with
freewheeling sex where Andrade had gained the mesmerizing power of
a cult leader with young girls who hoped for stardom.
</P>
<P>
   Although Ms. Trevi became one of Mexico's flashiest stars in the
early '90s because of her image of independence, a number of girls
who said they were lured into Andrade's harem have contended that
the singer was utterly dominated by him and helped him to commit
sexual abuse.
</P>
<P>
   The charges against Andrade and Ms. Trevi, whose real name is
Gloria de los Angeles Trevino, were first brought by the parents of
Karina Yapor Gomez, a young girl who was sent by her family when
she was 12 years old to study piano at a school run by Andrade.
</P>
<P>
   In 1997, when she was 15, Karina Yapor, who by then was living
in Spain with Andrade, Ms. Trevi and a half-dozen other young
girls, gave birth to a baby boy. Miss Yapor abandoned the emaciated
infant in a Spanish hospital, and her parents finally took him into
their care in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   In their criminal complaint, Miss Yapor's parents contended that
Andrade kidnapped their daughter and fathered her baby by force.
</P>
<P>
   Last December 16, Miss Yapor, who had not been home in two
years, suddenly turned up at the studios here of Televisa, the
national network where Ms. Trevi had been a star. In interviews so
wooden that she seemed to be speaking from a memorized text, Miss
Yapor called on her parents to drop the charges against Ms. Trevi
and Andrade.
</P>
<P>
   She offered her celebrity associates a ``very big apology,
because they were always very nice to me,'' and denied that the
rock manager was the father of her child.
</P>
<P>
   But Miss Yapor then returned to her parents' home in northern
Chihuahua state and went silent, and her family did not drop the
charges. At least four other young women have testified to police
since Miss Yapor's case became public that Andrade hit them and
forced them to have sex with him as a condition for continuing with
his music training.
</P>
<P>
   ``God always brings justice, both in heaven and on earth,''
Miguel Yapor, Karina's father, said in a telephone interview
Thursday. But he said it was not clear whether his daughter would
testify against Andrade in the upcoming trial.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
