singer from San Francisco. Since discovering the repertory of Piaf
in 1982, Ms. Bitton has helped produce a show about the legendary
French chanteuse for National Public Radio, consulted on a
television documentary, composed a play with music about Piaf's
friendship with Jean Cocteau, written the scenario for a
full-length Piaf ballet and, most decisively, learned to sing very
much like her idol. (The New York Times)
</P>
