<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; INTEL &LR;  _ If we've really entered the ``post-PC era,'' you wouldn't
know it by the financial results Intel posted yesterday. The Santa
Clara chip behemoth reported record revenues, net income and unit
shipments for the last quarter of 1999. Revenue for the fourth
quarter was $8.2 billion, up 8 percent from the year before and 12
percent from the third quarter of 1999. Net income was $2.1 billion
(61 cents per share), up from $2.06 billion (59 cents) a year ago.
By Henry Norr
</P>
