<SLUG> BC-OBIT-BREED-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ALLEN BREED, 72, DEVELOPER OF AUTO AIR BAGS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Fla.)   (bl)  
 By NICK RAVO   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Allen K. Breed, a pioneer in air bag technology for cars and
founder of one of the world's largest manufacturers of automobile
safety systems, Breed Technologies of Lakeland, Fla., died Dec. 13
at a hospital in Orlando, Fla. He was 72.
</P>
<P>
   Breed died of a heart attack but had also been suffering from
lung cancer, said his wife, Johnnie Breed.
</P>
<P>
   Breed Technologies, which Breed started in 1961 as Breed Corp.,
makes air bags and the firing mechanisms and sensors for them. The
company also makes seat belts and steering wheels.
</P>
<P>
   Breed retired two years ago and became chairman emeritus.
</P>
<P>
   Allen Kent Breed was born on July 27, 1927, in Chicago. He
earned a bachelor's degree from Northwestern University and joined
RCA. In the 1950s, he worked for the Gruen Watch Co. and founded
Waltham Engineering.
</P>
<P>
   His work at Breed Corp. in the 1960s focused on military safety
devices. He later applied the technology to automotive air bag
systems and created his first air bag sensor design for cars in
1968.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Breed was the third-largest supplier of automotive
safety systems in the world, with sales of $1.4 billion, behind TRW
and Autoliv. Last month, however, the company sought Chapter 11
protection in U.S. Bankruptcy Court.
</P>
<P>
   Breed was inducted into the Automotive Hall of Fame in Dearborn,
Mich., in 1999 in recognition of his invention of an air bag set
off by an electromechanical sensor, a forerunner of the electronic
sensors popular today.
</P>
<P>
   Besides his wife, Breed is survived by two daughters, Leslie
Breed Bates, of Massachusetts, and Daryl Breed Hoitt, of New
Hampshire, and two sons, Douglas Allen and Jeffrey Allen, both of
Florida; two stepsons, James Michael Cordell, of Utah, and Terry
Daniel Cordell, of Florida, and eight grandchildren.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
